  {title:"Actively managed ETFs charge 5-25x more than passive index funds", text:"ARKK (0.75%), JEPI (0.35%), and JEPQ (0.35%) show the premium for active management. Passive S&P 500 funds at 0.02-0.03% offer identical market exposure at a fraction of the cost. The fee gap narrows only for niche strategies."},
  {title:"Commodity ETFs are consistently the most expensive category", text:"Gold (GLD: 0.40%), silver (SLV: 0.50%), and oil (USO: 0.60%) ETFs carry higher expense ratios due to physical storage and futures contract rolling costs. GLDM at 0.10% is the notable exception for gold exposure."},
